The President will be conducting a town hall meeting at ElectraTherm in Reno, Nevada. ElectraTherm is a small renewable energy company that generates fuel-free, emission-free power from low to mid temperature waste heat. The company received a grant of approximately $982,000 from the Department of Energy to research and develop new methods of producing electricity. The audience at the town hall meeting will consist of ElectraTherm employees, local community college students and faculty, and various local leaders and invited guests.